50|$|If any of {{the files}} uses a sector which is marked as 'bad' by a disk utility then the <b>bad</b> <b>sector</b> of the file is remapped to a free sector and any {{unreadable}} data is lost. To avoid file corruption data recovery methods should be performed first if bad sectors are found (before being marked) by OS at file system level.|$|E
