50|$|Data erasure may {{not work}} {{completely}} on flash based media, such as Solid State Drives and USB Flash Drives, as these devices can store remnant data which is inaccessible to the erasure technique, and data can be retrieved from the individual flash memory chips inside the device.Data erasure through overwriting only works on hard drives that are functioning and writing to all <b>sectors.</b> <b>Bad</b> <b>sectors</b> cannot usually be overwritten, but may contain recoverable information. <b>Bad</b> <b>sectors,</b> however, may be invisible to the host system and thus to the erasing software. Disk encryption before use prevents this problem. Software-driven data erasure could also be compromised by malicious code.|$|R
